						<summary>

						<p>Written in modern characters and incomplete. It registers the building activities carried out at the front hall (<hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍapa</hi>) providing tiles to its roof and renewing of the walls in the temple of Mādavi-Īsvarar by Dāyar Koṭṭagaṉ son of Paḻaṉiyappa Koṭṭagaṉ, a vosalthy blacksmith, residing in Nilakkōṭṭai.</p>						

